The Young Entrepreneurs Academy is a nationwide program for high school students to create businesses of their own while working with mentors, instructors, and professionals to bring their dreams to life. This program is the only one of its kind in the Phoenix area. At the end of their 30-week program these students present their businesses in front of an investor panel and compete to bring their business to the national competition level. If they make it to nationals, they are competing for a chance to win a full-ride college scholarship, advertising for their business, and a chance to appear on the hit TV show, Shark Tank! The students we are mentoring are all at-risk Latino youth living under the poverty level, so this opportunity is absolutely life-changing for them!

summary: I LOVE what I do (and I'm not just saying that because everyone else does). For years, though, I struggled to figure out who I was and what impact I was going to make on the world. In 2010, fresh out of college, I moved to Arizona from a small town of 315 in Northern Minnesota (extra points for anyone who's actually heard of Taconite). Within less than year of making the move, I went through a HUGE life change, which forced me to start from scratch in figuring out who and what I wanted to be.By 2013, I had discovered my love for helping people better understand, appreciate, and market who they are and what they have to offer.
